  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Design & VM Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>We are seeking a highly skilled and creative Visual Merchandiser and Design Executive to lead the conceptualization, design, and implementation of innovative visual merchandising strategies across our retail stores. The ideal candidate will possess a unique blend of artistic vision, technical expertise, and industry experience gained from international markets, enabling them to elevate brand presence, drive customer engagement, and boost sales performance.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ol><li><strong>Concept Development & Design:</strong></li></ol><ul><li><li>Create cutting-edge visual merchandising concepts and store layouts that align with global brand standards and market trends.</li><li>Design and produce custom fixtures, displays, and props that enhance product presentation and customer experience.</li></li></ul><ol><li><strong>Strategy Implementation:</strong></li></ol><ul><li><li>Develop and execute seasonal campaigns, window displays, and in-store promotions that reflect international retail trends.</li><li>Ensure consistency in visual branding across all retail touchpoints while adapting strategies to the Singapore market.</li></li></ul><ol><li><strong>Cross-functional Collaboration:</strong></li></ol><ul><li><li>Work closely with marketing, retail operations, and product development teams to align visual merchandising with business objectives.</li><li>Train and guide store staff on visual standards, display techniques, and maintenance of merchandising setups.</li></li></ul><ol><li><strong>Market Analysis & Innovation:</strong></li></ol><ul><li><li>Conduct regular competitor analysis and market research to identify emerging trends and best practices from key global markets (e.g., Europe, North America, Japan).</li><li>Introduce innovative materials, technologies, or design methodologies not commonly used in Singapore’s retail landscape.</li></li></ul><ol><li><strong>Budget & Vendor Management:</strong></li></ol><ul><li><li>Manage the visual merchandising budget, sourcing materials and collaborating with specialized vendors or craftsmen from overseas when required.</li><li>Oversee the production and installation of visual elements, ensuring high quality and timely execution.</li></li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications & Experience</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Visual Merchandising, Interior Design, Fine Arts, or a related field.</li><li>Proficiency in design software such as Adobe Creative Suite, AutoCAD, SketchUp, or similar tools.</li><li>Strong portfolio showcasing innovative visual merchandising projects and creative campaigns.</li></ul>",
